  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 900 mg
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/gouda-pork-burgers-5e838042d6f999558005b0da
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve,
peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have
2 TBSP. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Grate 1 clove @Garlic{2%clove}. Halve
@Potato Buns{2}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon},
half the @Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), and a big
pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until browned and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a medium pan over medium heat. Add
sliced onion, @Sugar{3/4%teaspoon}, and salt. Cook, stirring, until browned and
softened, ~{10-15%minutes}. Stir in a squeeze of lime juice and
@sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

> TIP: Lower heat and add a splash of water if onion starts to burn.

While onion cooks, in a large #bowl{}, combine @Ground Pork{10%ounce},
minced onion, half the grated garlic, remaining paprika, ½ tsp sugar, and salt.
Form into two patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun. Heat a large
drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add patties and cook
until browned and cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. In the last 1-2
minutes of cooking, top each patty with @Gouda Cheese{2%slice}; cover
pan until cheese melts. Remove from pan and set aside.

Toast buns until golden. While buns toast, in a small bowl, combine
@Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lime
juice. Stir in as much lime zest and remaining grated garlic as you like.
Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: For a deeper flavor, toast in pan used for patties over medium heat.

Spread as much sauce as you like onto bottom buns; fill buns with patties and
sriracha onion. Divide burgers and potatoes between plates. Serve with any
remaining sauce for dipping and lime wedges on the side.